cs.AI, cs.GT, cs.SY, cs.RO, cs.LG. 

The paper proposes a game theoretical methodology to evaluate integration concepts of unmanned aerial systems (UAS) into the National Airspace System (NAS). It incorporates human pilot interactive decision making process using dynamic level-k reasoning concept and approximate reinforcement learning. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the following arXiv CS sub-categories: 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) for the use of reinforcement learning and modeling human pilot behavior. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) for the proposed game theoretical methodology. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) for the evaluation of UAS integration into the NAS. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) for the use of UAS equipped with sense and avoid algorithms. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) for the use of Neural Fitted Q Iteration, which is a machine learning method.
